workflow.name: Snooze Todoist tasks until 3 days before due date
workflow.description:
## Use case
This workflow snoozes any Todoist tasks, by moving them into a Snoozed todoist list and unsnoozes them 3 days before due date. Helps keep inbox clear only of tasks you need to worry about soon.
![Screenshot 20240228 at 19.40.42.png](fileId:754)

## How to setup
1. Add your Todoist creds
2. Create a Todoist project called `snoozed`
3. Set the project ids in the relevant nodes
4. Add due dates to your tasks in Inbox. Watch them disappear to `snoozed`. Set their date to tomorrow, watch it return to inbox.

## How to adjust this template
Adjust the timeline.. Maybe 3 days is too close for you. Works mostly for me :)

data.details:
The IF node can be used to implement binary conditional logic in your workflow. You can set up one-to-many conditions to evaluate each item of data being inputted into the node. That data will either evaluate to TRUE or FALSE and route out of the node accordingly.

This node has multiple types of conditions: Bool, String, Number, and Date & Time.

data.details: The Filter node can be used to filter items based on a condition. If the condition is met, the item will be passed on to the next node. If the condition is not met, the item will be omitted. Conditions can be combined together by AND(meet all conditions), or OR(meet at least one condition).
